    <p><img src="images/EvelynBarker.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" alt="Dr Jag Ahluwalia "width="300" height="200" align="left"><h2><center>Evelyn Barker</center></h2></p><center><p>Interim Chief Operating Officer (COO)</p></center>
    <div class="container text-center">
    <p>Evelyn is responsible for overseeing the effective daily management and performance of the PMC against local and national standards, and for the financial stewardship of the PMC’s services. 
Evelyn began her career as a clinical pharmacist working in a number of Jamaican hospitals before becoming chief pharmacist at University Hospital. She progressed through a number of operational divisional management roles ultimately becoming acting CEO in 2009. 
As well as holding the substantive post of chief operating officer / deputy CEO at NHS Foundation Trust, Evelyn brings a wealth of experience as an interim executive with over 10 years’ at executive board-level for foundation trusts across the country. </p>
